    "abstract": [],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": ", caused by the severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus-2 (SARS-CoV-2), multiple epidemiological assessments in countries from Asia, Europe, and North America have been published [3, 4] . Nevertheless, there are countries, with a rapid increase and a high number of cases, with a lack of studies. This is the case of Iran in the Middle East. For these reasons, we have developed epidemiological maps of cases but also of incidence rates using official populations, by provinces, for COVID-19",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 185,
                    "end": 188,
                    "text": "[3,",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF2"
                },
                {
                    "start": 189,
                    "end": 191,
                    "text": "4]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF3"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "in Iran using geographical information systems (GIS).",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Surveillance cases data from February 19 to March 9, 2020, officially reported by the Iranian health authorities were used to estimate the cumulated incidence rates using reference population data on SARS-CoV-2 confirmed infections (cases/100,000 pop) and to develop the maps by provinces, using the GIS software Kosmo\u00ae 3.1.",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "During the first 20 days of epidemics, 7,161 cases of COVID-19 were reported in the country, for a cumulated rate of 8.9 cases/100,000 population, reaching up to 1,234 cases during March 6, 2020 ( Figure 1 ). All the provinces have been affected, and rates ranged from 0.8 (Boushehr) to 61.8 cases/100,000 population (Qom) (Figure 1 ). At cases has been reported in the capital city, using GIS and estimating the incidence/attack rates per province, that one is placed as the seventh, having more cases per population at Qom, Semnan, and Markazi, among other provinces (Figure 1) .",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 197,
                    "end": 205,
                    "text": "Figure 1",
                    "ref_id": "FIGREF2"
                },
                {
                    "start": 323,
                    "end": 332,
                    "text": "(Figure 1",
                    "ref_id": "FIGREF2"
                },
                {
                    "start": 569,
                    "end": 579,
                    "text": "(Figure 1)",
                    "ref_id": "FIGREF2"
                }
            ],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "A recent study, based on imported cases from Iran, estimated that 18,300 (95% confidence interval: 3770 to 53,470) COVID-19 cases would have had to occur in the country [5] , assuming an outbreak duration of 1.5 months. Even if it were considered that all imported cases of Iran were identified in all states with certainty, the \"best case\" outbreak size was substantial (1820, 95% CI: 380-5320 cases), and far higher than reported case counts in February 2020. All confirmed cases in Saudi Arabia are imported from Iran and one from Iraq and other cases are close contacts to those confirmed cases. Imported cases from Iran have been diagnosed at Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq, Oman, Qatar, among other Asiatic countries, but also Georgia, Estonia, Belarus, and even New Zealand [6] .",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 169,
                    "end": 172,
                    "text": "[5]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF4"
                },
                {
                    "start": 772,
                    "end": 775,
                    "text": "[6]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF5"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "The capital city of Khorasan Razavi (3.1 cases/100,000 population), Mashhad, is the second-largest holy city in the world, attracting more than 20 million tourists and pilgrims every year [7, 8] , many of whom come to pay homage to the Imam Reza shrine (the eighth Shi'ite Imam).",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 188,
                    "end": 191,
                    "text": "[7,",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF6"
                },
                {
                    "start": 192,
                    "end": 194,
                    "text": "8]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF7"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Regardless of this epidemiological scenario, the Iran outbreak of COVID-19 is still beginning and complex. Authorities have limited travel, and schools and universities have closed, as also have occurred in Italy and Spain, until the start of the holiday for",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "Persian new year Nowruz on March 20, 2020, as measures for spreading of this coronavirus [7] .",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 89,
                    "end": 92,
                    "text": "[7]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF6"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        },
        {
            "text": "As there are severe limitations in the medical supplies available in the Iranian public health system to deal with the current SARS-CoV-2 outbreak, international support, additionally to be provided from the World Health Organization, is needed in the country to mitigate the impacts of this epidemic, and to avoid additional spreading. ",
            "cite_spans": [],
            "ref_spans": [],
            "section": ""
        }
